Control Data Corp. said it completed the sale of its Imprimis Technology data-storage products unit to Seagate Technology Inc. 

For the unit, Control said it received $250 million in cash, as well as 10.7 million new Seagate common shares and a $50 million promissory note. 

Control Data makes computer systems, services and data-storage equipment.
Scotts Valley, Calif.-based Seagate makes disk drives for computers. 

